column5: throwing out all kinds of fishing line friday friday is a good time to shine rant and rave leave this town behind start over with a new dream to climb  a million vacations is what you've got in mind    AND  Well I love her But I love to fish I spend all day out on this lake And hell is all I catch Today she met me at the door Said I would have to choose If I hit that fishin' hole today She'd be packin' all her things And she'd be gone by noon  Well I'm gonna miss her When I get home But right now I'm on this lakeshore And I'm sittin' in the sun I'm sure it'll hit me When I walk through that door tonight That I'm gonna miss her Oh, lookie there, I've got a bite  Now there's a chance that if I hurry I could beg her to stay But that water's right And the weather's perfect No tellin' what I might catch today  Well I'm gonna miss her When I get home But right now I'm on this lakeshore And I'm sittin' in the sun I'm sure it'll hit me When I walk through that door tonight That I'm gonna miss her Oh, lookie there, I've got a bite  Yeah, I'm gonna miss her Oh, lookie there, I've got a bite

'Mr. Brownstone' by Guns 'n Roses  " Use to do a little but a little wouldn't do so a little became more and more. Just keep trying to get a little better Said the little better than before"  Kinda how the act of fishing has been for me.  ehg

For some reason, when I hear the Doobie Brothers song "Black Water", I think of fishing at a particular time when I was fishing as a kid in Vermont. So I mellow out. <<<<Nothing to do with drugs>>>>.  How about you folks, is there such a song, and why??
Holy Diver, Ronnie James dio..  Listening to this will give you the creeps on a back bay still fishing at night when there isnt a soul for miles.
"I'm Gonna Miss Her" by Brad Paisley.  Love that song and I sang it tonight.

FISH ON!!! and, The Ol Diamond Back Sturgeon by Primus, just because of the lyrics.  That "I'm Going Fishing All the of the time and my baby's going fishing too," song at the intro of "Going Fishing," but then, at the end of the same show they have that different "Going Fishing" song.  On any given day either one will be humming in my head as I'm touring up river in the boat. lol  Travelling Riverside Blues by Zeppelin is likely my longest running and favorite going fishing song.  At the same time, whenever I hear it it reminds me of taking off in a plane on the runway at the airport in Moosonee.
"I'm Gonna Miss Her" by Brad Paisley.  I actually have that song as background music on one of my own fishing videos......I think its a great song.
"Down By the River"  by Neil Young great guitaring  Doug
"Song of the Coho"....Stompin' Tom Conners....
Luv the Doobies.  Most a ma guitar playin' is their songs from this album...
"fishin in the dark".Not sure of the artist. Kerry
Think this wierd, but hubby and I take a friend of ours fishing And we all start singing and whistling the song "Don't worry be Happy! and the funny part we start catching fish! Daisy_girl/Lorissa
Unbelieveable song by a sick band.  Rainbow in the dark is another one of my favourites.  Bobcaygen by the hip always makes me think of fishin

We used to hear "The Wizard" by Black Sabbath on the way up to many a fishing trip. Fish ON! Old Diamond Back Sturgeon and John the fisherman by Primus. The song at the beggining of the Cronzy show is Fishing Blues originally done by Taj Mahal. Thats the best fishing song ever IMO!
Kerry, Fishing In The Dark is one of my favorite songs too.   Nitty Gritty Dirt Band.  Tom.

You did not happen to be out fishing on the inner bay near long point this morning did you?   Just teasing  There were three guys about 12 feet away from us out on the water this morning and we got to listen to them singing Kareoke for the best part of an hr......Then i could not take anymore and had to move......The fish had stopped biteing i thought it was there singing...lmao....Turns out it was a nice size pike that had turned off the perch......They pulled it into they're boat and a beauty it was.
Neoprene waiters, Wide Spread Panic. All about fishing, they have a few other songs about fishing, but do you think I can find the CD. Nope.
Million Vacations Max Webster
Suishi Girl -The Tubes Green River - CCR Highway to Hell - AC/DC, FishnSled caught his PB last year as soon as the guitar riff started! HH
ah BITEME beat me to it  - Max Webster's "million vacations"  also a Van Morrison song, forget the real title but goes: "oh the water, oh ohhh the water....."

Fishin'  by Elvin Bishop Going up the country by Canned Heat Country Boy can Survive by Hank Williams Jr. Copperhead Road by Steve Earle Green River by CCR Swamp Music by Lynyrd Skynyrd Statesboro Blues by the Allman Brothers Bad to the Bone by George Thorogoode

Bohemian Rhapsody by Queen (A night at the opera) can't remember if it was 1975 or 76, any way we played that tape from the time we left till we got back didn't do alot of fishin that week but we did do about everything else, met a couple of babes at the camp. Oh to be young and care free again. I saw the guy that went up with me last week asked if I was ready for another trip like that again. hell yea.
How about "Country State Of Mind" by Hank Williams Jr.?

"Summer Nights" Van Halen from 5150  And this - the songs in the video that was put together from this summer's Tightlines Shootout by Steve (Rubee) What a blast that was being able to participate with the HOT REELS FISHING team.  http://video.google.com/videoplay?docid=4899949206834658386  Cheers, Gman
